rComments: Refuses to take questions or listen to her students, arrogant and her opinion is the only one that matters even if her opinion is contradicted by jurisprudence.

Aucune compétences pour être prof dans une université. Na pas à cœur la réussite étudiante ni lenvi denseigner, limpression quelle ne prend pas son emploi au sérieux. Dommage pour les étudiants. Cours pas nécessairement difficile.
WORST TEACHER I EVER HAD IN MY LIFE!! Avoid her at any cost....

Prof. Delisle clearly demonstrates a passion for social justice and to say it simply, "fighting the good fight". Attendance marks made class a must, but it was worth every minute of it. She's extremely knowledgable on the content and enjoys debating students on issues regarding social justice. Great professor!

Super easy A. She does not deserve all the flack she gets. She is so kind and caring and her lectures were interesting and super easy to follow! Would LOVE if she taught my future courses. A bit disorganized/absent minded at times, but you will miss her when you have tough profs in upper years. Loved her and her course. Highly recommend.

I took her my first semester & my first test with her i got a D & i was genuinely confused as to why lol i can laugh now that i look back & got a b+ in the course but marking def. got easier after first test ( maybe gauging the class?), it helps if she knows who you are & she's sweet so i think as long as youre there and taking notes it's fine

These ratings rly don't do her justice, I think she's one of the best profs I've had first year. She's super caring, very clear on what she excepts, and gives test and exam reviews with everything that's on the test. Very easy A if you pay attention and go over the material.

She is so sweet and a genuine person. Her lectures are entertaining and light and her course was easy. She was so funny without trying to be... in a good way. I would love to take another course with her!

I thought I would really enjoy Criminology prior to taking this course until I got into her class. It wasn't that she was a bad prof it just wasn't what I was expecting. A lot of the class involved talking about subject matter that didn't seem interesting but overall it was okay.
She's really caring and nice.. not sure why no one seems to like her. It was an easy credit and a fun and interesting course!

Reading these reviews scared me so much, but shes honestly not bad at all. She can be a little absent minded, but overall shes a really good teacher and a very nice person. I found her lectures stimulating and the course was an easy A.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: She was one of the best profs I had during first year! She shared her opinions and insight on real issues going on in the world and had us engage and exchange ideas with each other which I really appreciated. Her testing is super fair and reasonable. She made me want to take even more crim courses in the future.

Y'all need to relax - she's a great prof! Very kind, interesting lectures and is accessible outside of class. Her powerpoints are long but she adds interesting details on and relates it to famous people who are worth researching after class. Exam and the other 2 tests we did (including mid-term) were super easy. Exam is not based on the whole year.

Never stays on topic, often times it is hard to figure out what point she is even trying to make. Seems to enjoy making students feel stupid or mocking them for being smart. Seems very passionate about her work however it was rarely related to the topics being covered.
Super sweet, easy marker, and she has very clear grading criteria. It's hard to do bad in her class, like you really have to TRY to get anything under a B

Absolutely horrible. All she does is summarize the readings and put them on a 40 slide powerpoint. The content of the course itself had no relevance to the subject (crime prevention). She's ramble on oppression and privilege, bureaucracy, how the government controls everything, and how you shouldn't vaccinate your kids because of what she saw on FB

She's a very nice woman, who is obviously passionate about her work, very helpful in her office hours. Assignments/tests are straight forward/easy.  However, her lectures are hard to follow, her slides are even harder to follow and at times it is extremely hard to figure out which information will actually be relevant for exams.

She takes attendance way too seriously, she remembers faces and sometimes takes attendance. Her lectures are very boring and she goes off topic A LOT. Her 2 midterms are very unfair (half the class failed) and has 10% participation and 15% assignment (somewhat made up for the bad midterms). I WOULD NOT RECOMMEND TAKING THIS COURSE WITH THIS PROF.
The worst teacher ever, please avoid

Horrible prof. Unclear expectations, and she is rude to make matters worse. Filed a group complaint to the Dean for  her poor teaching methods as well as her prejudice. Makes students feel stupid and is eager to remind them of so. Marking is awful and her lectures are unfounded and  I question the validity of what she is teaching.
Omg, pire prof ever. Elle toujours confuse quand elle explique. Pire powerpoint. Au moins c'est facile d'avoir de bonnes notes avec elle!

Elle est une tough grader, donc soyez prêt à travailler relativement plus fort que dans les autres cours. Good prof, nice woman. Classes were a little boring but she gives clear grading criteria for every exam/quiz. I am french immersion, and for any french immersion students I would recommend her class. She is easy to understand and the material is clear.

This professor is incompetent. Her powerpoint slideshows would have sentences that were half in English, half in French so she obviously payed no attention to the material she was giving us. Disorganised, comes to class forgetting her powerpoints, needs to use google midlecture because she doesnt know what she's talking about, rambles. Class is only about politics, doesn't talk aboout criminology even though it's a CRM class

Multiple grammar mistakes, unorganized powerpoints with english slides (it's a french course), no relation between the lectures and the class description, always asking us to translate words for her or find words (she couldn't remember Bin Laden's name..). Excellent!
Le cours d'abolitionisme était excellent! Il est évident que le sujet lui tient à coeur et cela se voit aux travers de ses cours. Si vous étudiez et que vous comprenez, ses examens sont faciles.

Claire est une professeure géniale. Elle est drôle, passionnée par l'abolitionnisme et une activiste affirmée. Elle ne mâche pas ses mots, ses examens sont loin d'être difficiles puisqu'Ils sont majoritairement basé sur ses powerpoint. Madame Delisle s'est nettement améliorer comparativement au cours de justice et normes pénales. L'abolitionnisme est sa branche, elle est donc un peu plus claire dans ses explications. L'examen de mi-session n'est pas si difficile et elle est ouverte à ce qu'on s'oppose à son opinion dans l'examen.

Very sweet and helpful. She's very passionate about what she does. She's a bit slow on the technology part of class (distance education students, using YouTube, etc) but students were more than happy to help. It just took a bit longer. The class did poorly on one assignment and she created another replacement assignment which I am so grateful for.

Professeure qui n'a aucune connaissance en criminologie et n'est certainement pas capable de répondre aux questions. Une chance pour l'assistante de cours! Si possible, essaie d'éviter de prendre un cours avec elle. Pire professeure jamais eu.

The prof was scattered and often confused, not remembering what she was talking about or why. The lectures given were irrelevant and getting a good grade in this course was based mostly on dumb luck.

The class is very unwelcoming. You must share the same beliefs as the prof or you probably shouldn't speak in class at all (which is what I did). Dry lectures that are very difficult to pay attention to. Awkward powerpoint format. I would not recommend this course or this prof.

Pire cours à vie.! La prof n'est jamais vraiment prête, les examens n'ont aucun rapport avec la matière vue en classe.  Il n'y a aucune cohérence dans son cours. What the professor says is realy confusing, plus she is not well organized. Some time she will have problem with the computer, or she will lost some documents, not be on sceduls, etc.
